1:28 PM Prosecuting attorney Angela M Wilson in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Jessica Rose Bennett appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman in court for Jessica Rose Bennett. Attorney/Defendant acknowledges receipt of the complaint, waives a formal reading, enters pleas of not guilty to the misdemeanor count(s), and requests a preliminary hearing. State asks for $2,500 cash. No use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription. State notes charges alleged, absconder status from probation since 2015, and currently has a probation hold. Recites defendant's prior criminal history. Attorney Hoffman indicates that the defendant is a lifelong resident of St. Louis county, MN and has family and employment in the area. Defendant can post up to $500. 

Court orders $1500 cash. No use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 6, 2022 at 10:30 am.
